{{afc comment|1=Page originally made on english wikipedia in draftspace. g13 deleted and archived on everybodywiki. Go to [[:en:Wikipedia:Requests for undeletion]] to request undeletion of original page [[:en:draft:Softening of Evil Hearts]] and import the revisions to here for attribution. View on everybodywiki here [[:every:Softening of Evil Hearts|Softening of Evil Hearts]]. [[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 21:01, 16 February 2025 (UTC)}}{{draft}} [[File:Umyagchenie_zlukh_serdets.jpg|thumb]]<!--Softening of Evil Hearts-->{{Interlanguage link|12=draft|Softening of Evil Hearts|ru|Умягчение злых сердец}} is a Marian apparition<ref name=":0" />.<!--Content from {{ill|Folk_Orthodoxy|every|8=en|12=draft}}<!--{{s11}}---><!--Softening of Evil Hearts-->--> {{ill|ru:Умягчение злых сердец|every|8=en|12=draft}}<!--Softening of Evil Hearts-->In {{ill|Bailichka|lt=bylichka|every|8=en|12=draft}}<!--Softening of Evil Hearts-->and spiritual verses, Paraskeva Friday complains that she is not honored by not observing the prohibition on Fridays – they prick her with spindles, spin her hair, clog her eyes {{ill|Shives|lt=Kostrakostra|every|8=en|12=draft}}<!--Softening of Evil Hearts-->. According to beliefs, {{ill|Paraskeva Friday|every|8=en|12=draft}}<!--Softening of Evil Hearts-->is depicted on icons with spokes or spindles sticking out of her chest (cf. images of {{Interlanguage link|12=draft|Holy Virgin Mary of Seven Swords|ru|Семистрельная икона|lt=Seven-Strength Icon|Holy Virgin Mary of Seven Swords=Holy Virgin Mary of Seven Swords}} , {{Interlanguage link|12=draft|Softening of Evil Hearts|ru|Умягчение злых сердец}}).<ref name=":0">Paraskeva Pyatnitsa / Levkievskaya E. E., Tolstaya S. M. // Slavic Antiquities : Ethnolinguistic Dictionary: in 5 volumes / under the general ed. N. I. Tolstoy ; Institute of Slavic Studies RAS . - <abbr>M .</abbr> : Interd. relations , 2009. - V. 4: P (Crossing the water) - S (Sieve). - S. 631-633. - {{ISBN|5-7133-0703-4|978-5-7133-1312-8}}</ref>
==Overview==
'''Umyagchenie Zlykh Serdets Icon of the Mother of God''' (Икона Богородицы «Умягчение злых сердец») — a revered {{ill|icon|ru|икона|12=draft}} of the {{ill|Mother of God|ru|Богородица|12=draft}}, also known as ''Simeon’s Prophecy''. It depicts the prophecy of {{ill|Simeon the God-Receiver|ru|Симеон Богоприимец|12=draft}} spoken during the {{ill|Presentation of Jesus at the Temple|ru|Сретение Господне|12=draft}}: {{НЗ|“Behold, this Child is destined for the fall and rising of many in Israel… and a sword will pierce through your own soul also.”|Lk|2:34|-35}}
The image likely originated from southwestern Rus', though its early history is unknown<ref name="Dmitrieva">{{Cite web|url=https://pravoslavie.ru/1915.html|title=Nadezhda Dmitrieva. Icon of the Mother of God 'Umyagchenie Zlykh Serdets'|access-date=2022-08-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220830195319/https://pravoslavie.ru/1915.html|archive-date=2022-08-30}}</ref>.
== Iconography == The Mother of God is depicted with seven swords piercing her heart—three on each side and one below—symbolizing the fullness of sorrow experienced during her life<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pravmir.ru/pravoslavnyj-kalendar/icons1/ikona-umyagchenie.html|title=Icon of the Mother of God 'Umyagchenie Zlykh Serdets'|archive-url=https://www.pravmir.ru/pravoslavnyj-kalendar/icons1/ikona-umyagchenie.html|archive-date=2022-08-30}}</ref>. In some versions, the Christ Child is depicted on her lap<ref name="Dmitrieva"/>.
The icon is closely related to the {{ill|Semistrelnaya Icon|ru|Семистрельная икона Божией Матери|12=draft}}, differing only in the arrangement of the swords—three on one side and four on the other<ref name="Dmitrieva"/>.
The feast day is observed on the {{ill|Sunday of All Saints|ru|Неделя всех святых|12=draft}}.
== Hymnography == A traditional prayer before the icon: {{начало цитаты}} O Most Sorrowful Mother of God, higher than all daughters of the earth in purity and suffering, accept our sorrowful sighs and shelter us under Your mercy. You alone are our refuge and intercessor before Your Son. Help us, guide us, and lead us to the Heavenly Kingdom. Amen. {{конец цитаты}}
== Veneration == Believers pray before the icon for peace, reconciliation, and deliverance from enmity and persecution. It is also invoked for healing from cholera, lameness, and paralysis.
